comments: Curry (GSW) briefly places a hand on Sabonis' (SAC) side and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Thompson (GSW) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Payton II (GSW) rests a hand on Monk's (SAC) back while moving alongside his path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Curry (GSW) reaches in and initiates contact with Sabonis' (SAC) left arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Sabonis (SAC) contests the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Payton II's (GSW) left arm after the release.
Sabonis (SAC) is establishing screening position in Curry's (GSW) path and Curry initiates marginal contact as he brings his arm along Sabonis' side.
Thompson (GSW) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Sabonis (SAC) is firming up on his left foot as he establishes himself in Payton II's (GSW) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Green (GSW) makes contact with the ball during Monk's (SAC) driving shot attempt.
Thompson (GSW) contests the jump shot attempt and incidental hand on ball contact occurs with Barnes (SAC) that dislodges the ball.
SAC commits a shot clock violation.
Monk (SAC) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Curry's (GSW) right arm after the release.
Payton II (GSW) and Monk (SAC) briefly engage and disengage, resulting in marginal contact off-ball.
Payton II (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it away from Monk (SAC) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Murray (SAC) is retreating as he defends Curry (GSW) and marginal contact occurs with Payton II (GSW) off-ball as the two come together during the pick.
Barnes (SAC) briefly slides his hand across and off Curry's (GSW) front and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Mitchell (SAC) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Sabonis (SAC) briefly grasps Wiggins' (GSW) right arm before releasing while the inbound pass is made and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
